        <h1>1.2 Historical Development of Quantum Theory</h1>
        <p>The transition from classical to quantum theory was marked by the realization that energy is quantized. Max Planck’s study of blackbody radiation led to the formula:</p>

        <div class="equation-box">
            $$E = h\nu$$
        </div>

        <p>This section explores how these historical milestones shifted our understanding of the microscopic world, moving away from deterministic Newtonian paths to probabilistic wave functions.</p>

