        <h1>1.3 Davisson-Germer Experiment</h1>
        <p>The experimental confirmation of matter waves came when Davisson and Germer observed electron diffraction from a nickel crystal. This proved that electrons behave as waves under certain conditions.</p>
        
        

        <p>The result matched the predicted de Broglie wavelength for electrons accelerated through a potential $V$:</p>
        <div class="equation-box">
            $$\lambda = \frac{h}{\sqrt{2meV}}$$
        </div>

