    <div class="a4-page" id="page6">
        <h1>1.6 Uncertainty Principle</h1>
        <p>Heisenberg's Uncertainty Principle states that one cannot measure the position ($x$) and momentum ($p$) of a particle with absolute precision simultaneously.</p>

        <div class="equation-box">
            $$\Delta x \cdot \Delta p \geq \frac{\hbar}{2}$$
        </div>

        <p>Applications include explaining why electrons do not fall into the nucleus and estimating the zero-point energy of a harmonic oscillator.</p>

